            <link>https://kotaku.com/kotaku-s-best-game-tips-for-the-week-july-05-2025-1851785671</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/kotaku%E2%80%99s-best-game-tips-for-the-week-july-05-2025.1236450/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="11f9f01be82d92cd230ffd362636a7dc" data-recommend-id="image://11f9f01be82d92cd230ffd362636a7dc" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Dogubomb / Timothy Monbleau / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Samuel Moreno / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->FromSoftware / George Yang / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Capcom / Samuel Moreno / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Sandfall Interactive / George Yang / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Capcom / Samuel Moreno / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="11f9f01be82d92cd230ffd362636a7dc" data-recommend-id="image://11f9f01be82d92cd230ffd362636a7dc" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>If you’re stuck on a tricky boss fight or a challenging puzzle, or just want to make the most of your time with a new release, we’ve got you covered. Here are some of the tips we found most helpful this week.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="67146257314896c0bdee5e44529746a3" data-recommend-id="image://67146257314896c0bdee5e44529746a3" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot from a cutscene in Blue Prince. The protagonist Simon is walking into the Security Room." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot from a cutscene in Blue Prince. The protagonist Simon is walking into the Security Room." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Dogubomb / Timothy Monbleau / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="67146257314896c0bdee5e44529746a3" data-recommend-id="image://67146257314896c0bdee5e44529746a3" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot from a cutscene in Blue Prince. The protagonist Simon is walking into the Security Room." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>If you browse the catalogue of games available as part of Sony’s PlayStation Plus service, you’ll see that the critically acclaimed puzzle sensation <em>Blue Prince </em>is<em> </em>classified as a “quick adventure.” This is a lie on par with saying that you can find a Mew under the truck by the S.S. Anne in the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-card-stolen-charizard-attack-crime-1851778231&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-card-stolen-charizard-attack-crime-1851778231">first generation <em>Pokémon</em></a></span><em> </em>games, or that the reason <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/life-strange-double-exposure-award-gdc-2025-layoffs-1851771282&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/life-strange-double-exposure-award-gdc-2025-layoffs-1851771282">game developers keep getting laid off</a></span> is because games are too dang cheap and not because <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/bungie-pete-parsons-layoffs-classic-cars-sony-buyout-de-1851610196&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/bungie-pete-parsons-layoffs-classic-cars-sony-buyout-de-1851610196">CEOs are blowing the budgets on classic cars</a></span>. I’ve literally spent more time uncovering <em>Blue Prince</em>’s secrets than I’ve spent <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/how-long-is-visions-of-mana-square-enix-rpg-1851635405&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/how-long-is-visions-of-mana-square-enix-rpg-1851635405">100%-ing full-length RPGs</a></span>, and it would be truly tragic for someone looking for a short romp to fall down a bottomless rabbit hole such as this.<!-- --> - Timothy Monbleau <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/blue-prince-how-long-to-beat-room-46-tutorial-puzzles-1851785424&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/blue-prince-how-long-to-beat-room-46-tutorial-puzzles-1851785424">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="44325e9c88b4a103080470cc77427fe6" data-recommend-id="image://44325e9c88b4a103080470cc77427fe6" data-format="png" data-width="3840" data-height="2160" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Link looks out over Hyrule from a Sky Island." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Link looks out over Hyrule from a Sky Island." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="44325e9c88b4a103080470cc77427fe6" data-recommend-id="image://44325e9c88b4a103080470cc77427fe6" data-format="png" data-width="3840" data-height="2160" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Link looks out over Hyrule from a Sky Island." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Whether you’re a fan of the <em>Legend of Zelda </em>franchise or are simply looking for a thrilling open-world game to sink your teeth into on your fancy new Switch 2, you can rest assured that 2023’s <em>Tears of the Kingdom</em> can provide a hell of a good time. This is a dense, lengthy title that can keep you busy for weeks or longer. But if you like to plan ahead or are just curious about just how long it takes to beat Link’s massive second Nintendo Switch outing, let’s take a look.<!-- --> - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/tears-of-the-kingdom-zelda-switch-2-upgrade-how-long-1851785468&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/tears-of-the-kingdom-zelda-switch-2-upgrade-how-long-1851785468">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="4fe061b49b5bfaa4434c642ae016a420" data-recommend-id="image://4fe061b49b5bfaa4434c642ae016a420" data-format="gif" data-width="800" data-height="450" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An animated gif shows fantasy character battling sentient plants." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An animated gif shows fantasy character battling sentient plants." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Gif<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvelous / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4fe061b49b5bfaa4434c642ae016a420" data-recommend-id="image://4fe061b49b5bfaa4434c642ae016a420" data-format="gif" data-width="800" data-height="450" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An animated gif shows fantasy character battling sentient plants." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The latest entry in the long-running<em> Rune Factory</em> series is here. This time, <em>Rune Factory: Guardians of Azuma </em>takes players to an eastern setting inspired by ancient Japanese culture instead of the usual fantasy and steampunk-ish settings from the previous games.<!-- --> - George Yang <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/rune-factory-guardians-of-azuma-how-long-story-farming-1851785504&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/rune-factory-guardians-of-azuma-how-long-story-farming-1851785504">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="f2414504e486f6dc2b59a724a78baff9" data-recommend-id="image://f2414504e486f6dc2b59a724a78baff9" data-format="jpg" data-width="1260" data-height="708" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Promotional art for Breath of the Wild shows Link looking out at Hyrule." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Promotional art for Breath of the Wild shows Link looking out at Hyrule." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="f2414504e486f6dc2b59a724a78baff9" data-recommend-id="image://f2414504e486f6dc2b59a724a78baff9" data-format="jpg" data-width="1260" data-height="708" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Promotional art for Breath of the Wild shows Link looking out at Hyrule." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>There are so many recipes in <em>The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild</em> that it’s difficult to lock down the objectively best options for every scenario, especially when there are so many variations to consider. But we’ve compiled some undeniably useful recipes that everyone should know, so here’s to hoping they can make your time with the game a bit easier. Let’s get cookin’.<!-- --> - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/zelda-breath-of-the-wild-botw-recipes-switch-2-mushroom-1851785344&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/zelda-breath-of-the-wild-botw-recipes-switch-2-mushroom-1851785344">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="f095301951fd2bd01bbb19a78ebcb5c9" data-recommend-id="image://f095301951fd2bd01bbb19a78ebcb5c9" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Bowser drives along Baby Luigi, Wario, and other racers." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Bowser drives along Baby Luigi, Wario, and other racers." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Samuel Moreno / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="f095301951fd2bd01bbb19a78ebcb5c9" data-recommend-id="image://f095301951fd2bd01bbb19a78ebcb5c9" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Bowser drives along Baby Luigi, Wario, and other racers." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Choosing who to race with isn’t just an <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/mario-kart-world-outfits-mario-peach-luigi-yoshi-toad-1851785556&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/mario-kart-world-outfits-mario-peach-luigi-yoshi-toad-1851785556">aesthetic choice</a></span> in <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/mario-kart-world-best-tips-boxes-coins-grinding-drift-1851783857&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/mario-kart-world-best-tips-boxes-coins-grinding-drift-1851783857"><em>Mario Kart World</em></a></span>. Every character belongs to a particular weight class and their set stats change when paired with the various vehicles. <!-- --> - Samuel Moreno <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/mario-kart-world-kart-best-stats-weight-vehicle-1851785613&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/mario-kart-world-kart-best-stats-weight-vehicle-1851785613">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="86f2c39506146f958288c8a0668a0792" data-recommend-id="image://86f2c39506146f958288c8a0668a0792" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1077" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="ES Fulghor leaps into the air to deliver and attack." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="ES Fulghor leaps into the air to deliver and attack." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->FromSoftware / George Yang / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="86f2c39506146f958288c8a0668a0792" data-recommend-id="image://86f2c39506146f958288c8a0668a0792" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1077" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="ES Fulghor leaps into the air to deliver and attack." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Nightreign</em> players arguably consider Fulghor, Champion of Nightglow to be one of the hardest Day-Three Bosses in the game. With the introduction of Everdark Sovereigns (ES), which are beefed up versions of current bosses, Fulghor is back once again to terrorize you.<!-- --> - George Yang <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/elden-rign-nightreign-everdark-es-sovereign-fulghor-1851785340&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/elden-rign-nightreign-everdark-es-sovereign-fulghor-1851785340">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="5cacc0e4a6d13db571707a937ef394f3" data-recommend-id="image://5cacc0e4a6d13db571707a937ef394f3" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Chargin' Chuck holds up a hand while racing on a water vehicle." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Chargin' Chuck holds up a hand while racing on a water vehicle." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="5cacc0e4a6d13db571707a937ef394f3" data-recommend-id="image://5cacc0e4a6d13db571707a937ef394f3" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Chargin' Chuck holds up a hand while racing on a water vehicle." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>One of the biggest additions to Mario Kart World is the addition of loads of enemies and NPCs as kart drivers to help expand the game’s already massive roster. From Sunshine’s Piantas to the football gear-clad Chargin’ Chuck, there’s loads of new drivers to unlock that have never been playable before. But how do you unlock all of Bowser’s baddies? We’ll help you know the answer, and figure out how to unlock them quickly.<!-- --> - Parker Johnson <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/mario-kart-world-npc-spike-swoop-dolphin-peepa-pianta-1851785560&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/mario-kart-world-npc-spike-swoop-dolphin-peepa-pianta-1851785560">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="1d9150c35c4e49cb04fac57fbae35c68" data-recommend-id="image://1d9150c35c4e49cb04fac57fbae35c68" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A hunter in Rey Dau Gamma Armor wields a Rey Dau-made Bow." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A hunter in Rey Dau Gamma Armor wields a Rey Dau-made Bow." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Capcom / Samuel Moreno / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="1d9150c35c4e49cb04fac57fbae35c68" data-recommend-id="image://1d9150c35c4e49cb04fac57fbae35c68" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A hunter in Rey Dau Gamma Armor wields a Rey Dau-made Bow." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Just like previous entries, armor in <em>Monster Hunter Wilds</em> is crucial for both <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-appearance-cosmetics-transmog-1851772498&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-appearance-cosmetics-transmog-1851772498">style</a></span> and <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-how-do-skills-work-talismans-1851769023&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-how-do-skills-work-talismans-1851769023">strategy</a></span>. While they might look the same, choosing between an Alpha or Beta version of an armor is important. The choice is even more difficult now that the first Gamma set has been added.<!-- --> - Samuel Moreno <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-mhw-armor-alpha-beta-gamma-arch-1851785351&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-mhw-armor-alpha-beta-gamma-arch-1851785351">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="39920f2db5543e3cd4447daac631a7df" data-recommend-id="image://39920f2db5543e3cd4447daac631a7df" data-format="png" data-width="960" data-height="540" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Lune stands before Blanche." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Lune stands before Blanche." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sandfall Interactive / George Yang / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="39920f2db5543e3cd4447daac631a7df" data-recommend-id="image://39920f2db5543e3cd4447daac631a7df" data-format="png" data-width="960" data-height="540" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Lune stands before Blanche." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>In <em>Clair Obscur: Expedition 33</em>, there are a total of 10 Nevron quests. By completing these quests, you can unlock the “Aiding the Enemy” achievement or trophy.<!-- --> - George Yang <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-aiding-the-enemy-blanche-1851785361&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-aiding-the-enemy-blanche-1851785361">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="6ed1542458a85f7922b71172b045dcc6" data-recommend-id="image://6ed1542458a85f7922b71172b045dcc6" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Lala Barina with a blue Tempered Wound faces off against a hunter." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A Lala Barina with a blue Tempered Wound faces off against a hunter." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Capcom / Samuel Moreno / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="6ed1542458a85f7922b71172b045dcc6" data-recommend-id="image://6ed1542458a85f7922b71172b045dcc6" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Lala Barina with a blue Tempered Wound faces off against a hunter." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Between the chance-based drop system to the different conditions that certain monsters spawn in, some things require a bit of luck in <em>Monster Hunter Wilds</em>. This can make grinding out materials for your next set of badass weaponry and <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-appearance-cosmetics-transmog-1851772498&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-appearance-cosmetics-transmog-1851772498">pretty armor</a></span> a longer process than you’d like.<!-- --> - Samuel Moreno <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-investigations-farm-monster-1851785212&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-investigations-farm-monster-1851785212">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div><br/><br/>https://kotaku.com/kotaku-s-best-game-tips-for-the-week-july-05-2025-1851785671]]></content:encoded>
