            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="4b72d00c0b8fd692f9f7e18405790145" data-recommend-id="image://4b72d00c0b8fd692f9f7e18405790145" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Microsoft<!-- -->, <!-- -->11bit Studios<!-- -->, <!-- -->FromSoftware / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->PlayStation / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->The Pokémon Company / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Blizzard Entertainment<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo<!-- -->, <!-- -->Epic Games / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Romero Games<!-- -->, <!-- -->Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Rockstar Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4b72d00c0b8fd692f9f7e18405790145" data-recommend-id="image://4b72d00c0b8fd692f9f7e18405790145" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>From mergers to memes, the landscape of interactive entertainment is always in motion. Here’s your cheat sheet for the week’s most important stories in gaming.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="1ed531513837cd16297cc6e0514becbe" data-recommend-id="image://1ed531513837cd16297cc6e0514becbe" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Microsoft Gaming CEO Phil Spencer appears at Comic Con Experience (CCXP23) in Brazil." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Microsoft Gaming CEO Phil Spencer appears at Comic Con Experience (CCXP23) in Brazil." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Microsoft Gaming CEO Phil Spencer appears at Comic Con Experience (CCXP23) in Brazil.</figcaption><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Microsoft</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="1ed531513837cd16297cc6e0514becbe" data-recommend-id="image://1ed531513837cd16297cc6e0514becbe" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Microsoft Gaming CEO Phil Spencer appears at Comic Con Experience (CCXP23) in Brazil." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/xbox-prices-layoffs-next-gen-hardware-ps5-1851784992&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/xbox-prices-layoffs-next-gen-hardware-ps5-1851784992">Reports and rumors</a></span> of massive layoffs at Xbox have been building since late last month, and the first blood has now been spilled. <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-07-02/microsoft-begins-deep-job-cuts-across-xbox-division?sref=P6Q0mxvj&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-07-02/microsoft-begins-deep-job-cuts-across-xbox-division?sref=P6Q0mxvj" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Bloomberg</em> reports</a></span> that <em>Candy Crush </em>maker King is cutting 200 employees, or roughly 10 percent of its 2,000-person headcount, while multiple games across various Xbox studios, including <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/xbox-reportedly-cancels-that-cool-looking-perfect-dark-1851785531?rev=1751476543549&amp;_gl=1*1w25uuv*_ga*NjQ4ODc3OTQxLjE3NDgwMDgwOTM.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NTE0NzM0NDMkbzMkZzEkdDE3NTE0NzY3MjEkajYwJGwwJGgw&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/xbox-reportedly-cancels-that-cool-looking-perfect-dark-1851785531?rev=1751476543549&amp;_gl=1*1w25uuv*_ga*NjQ4ODc3OTQxLjE3NDgwMDgwOTM.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NTE0NzM0NDMkbzMkZzEkdDE3NTE0NzY3MjEkajYwJGwwJGgw">the <em>Perfect Dark </em>reboot</a></span>, have been canceled. <!-- --> - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/latest-round-of-mass-layoffs-at-xbox-begin-with-200-job-1851785492&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/latest-round-of-mass-layoffs-at-xbox-begin-with-200-job-1851785492">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="404a53f5cf885c88476c7df3b1e3d721" data-recommend-id="image://404a53f5cf885c88476c7df3b1e3d721" data-format="jpg" data-width="1568" data-height="882" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Clones appear in pink track suits in a science station. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Clones appear in pink track suits in a science station. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->11bit Studios</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="404a53f5cf885c88476c7df3b1e3d721" data-recommend-id="image://404a53f5cf885c88476c7df3b1e3d721" data-format="jpg" data-width="1568" data-height="882" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Clones appear in pink track suits in a science station. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>The Alters</em> is a narrative-driven sci-fi survival management sim about a research facility populated by clones. It released in June to positive reviews, with critics praising it for wedding interesting character interactions to the usual management sim churn. Now it’s getting flamed for incorporating AI slop. The studio behind it took to social media to defend itself, saying that a viral screenshot of an LLM text-generating prompt was an isolated incident and was never supposed to be kept in the game. <!-- --> - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/the-alters-gen-ai-slop-scifi-management-sim-11bit-1851785372&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/the-alters-gen-ai-slop-scifi-management-sim-11bit-1851785372">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="dc73249fc04b6d20f5077236e5ef62b7" data-recommend-id="image://dc73249fc04b6d20f5077236e5ef62b7" data-format="png" data-width="1324" data-height="745" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An Ironeye looks at a disconnect warning. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An Ironeye looks at a disconnect warning. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->FromSoftware / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="dc73249fc04b6d20f5077236e5ef62b7" data-recommend-id="image://dc73249fc04b6d20f5077236e5ef62b7" data-format="png" data-width="1324" data-height="745" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An Ironeye looks at a disconnect warning. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>I leave <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/elden-ring-nightreign-review-in-progress-difficulty-1851782700&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/elden-ring-nightreign-review-in-progress-difficulty-1851782700"><em>Elden Ring Nightreign</em> matches</a></span> all the time. Sometimes I’m playing with friends and we botch the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/elden-ring-nightreign-evergaol-key-darkdrift-relic-1851785161&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/elden-ring-nightreign-evergaol-key-darkdrift-relic-1851785161">first Evergaol mini-boss</a></span> at level 2. Sometimes I’m playing with internet randos and the Recluse runs off to farm crystals without telling anyone and we get wiped multiple times by <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.reddit.com/r/Nightreign/comments/1l4114k/i_hate_this_enemy_in_particular_since_elden_ring/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Nightreign/comments/1l4114k/i_hate_this_enemy_in_particular_since_elden_ring/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">the Perfumer’s crossbow-wielding glass cannon henchmen</a></span>. Every time I leave, the game warns me not to. “Don’t do it, don’t you dare do it!” it chides me. These are empty threats. I know because I lob them at my kids all the time. I have yet to see any evidence that I’ve actually been penalized for leaving matches, something I’ve occasionally done multiple times in a row. <!-- --> - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/elden-ring-nightreign-leave-abandon-penalty-matchmaking-1851785434&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/elden-ring-nightreign-leave-abandon-penalty-matchmaking-1851785434">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="0217177b63e460bc9087add65822defd" data-recommend-id="image://0217177b63e460bc9087add65822defd" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->PlayStation / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="0217177b63e460bc9087add65822defd" data-recommend-id="image://0217177b63e460bc9087add65822defd" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>A big summer sale is currently happening on the PlayStation Store, with a ton of PS5 games discounted to $25 or less. </p><p>Summer means hot weather, sweaty shirts, cookouts, and a bunch of video game deals. <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/steam-sale-2025-best-big-deals-schedule-i-battlefront-1851785167&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/steam-sale-2025-best-big-deals-schedule-i-battlefront-1851785167">Valve is currently running its big Steam summer sale</a></span>. EA has a big summer sale happening, too. And PlayStation, not wanting to be left out, has also flipped the switch on a bunch of big summer deals for PS5 games. <!-- --> - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ps5-psn-summer-july-sale-best-biggest-deals-discounts-1851785543&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ps5-psn-summer-july-sale-best-biggest-deals-discounts-1851785543">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="156b06fefd42c72c1ab9a7c13f98a0a2" data-recommend-id="image://156b06fefd42c72c1ab9a7c13f98a0a2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The awful sight of Geodude and his evolutions, sewn together." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The awful sight of Geodude and his evolutions, sewn together." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->The Pokémon Company / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="156b06fefd42c72c1ab9a7c13f98a0a2" data-recommend-id="image://156b06fefd42c72c1ab9a7c13f98a0a2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The awful sight of Geodude and his evolutions, sewn together." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>My eyes! What is this monstrosity?! Fetch me wooden stakes, holy water, silver bullets, shotguns, <em>anything</em>! Or has the Pokémon Company (TPCi) hired David Cronenberg to design its latest batch of plushies? <!-- --> - John Walker <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-center-plush-geodude-graveler-golem-cave-1851785591&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-center-plush-geodude-graveler-golem-cave-1851785591">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="50631ba28e9a853c550b4d2fe070ea22" data-recommend-id="image://50631ba28e9a853c550b4d2fe070ea22" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Reaper holding his mythic weapon." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Reaper holding his mythic weapon." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Blizzard Entertainment</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="50631ba28e9a853c550b4d2fe070ea22" data-recommend-id="image://50631ba28e9a853c550b4d2fe070ea22" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Reaper holding his mythic weapon." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Overwatch 2 </em>has been on a hot streak as of late, with excellent additions like the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/overwatch-2-season-17-perk-bug-all-perks-glitch-equip-1851785076&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/overwatch-2-season-17-perk-bug-all-perks-glitch-equip-1851785076">Perks system</a></span> that lets you upgrade a hero throughout a match, and the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/overwatch-2-perks-stadium-season-15-spotlight-preview-1851761919&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/overwatch-2-perks-stadium-season-15-spotlight-preview-1851761919">Stadium mode</a></span> that lets you create off-the-wall builds for each hero over the course of a seven-round game. The shooter just entered its 17th season, bringing with it a retro-game-themed battle pass, new heroes and maps for Stadium, and map voting across all modes. All of that sounds good on paper, but the addition of map voting and the way Blizzard implemented the system has split the community. After playing around with it myself, I yearn for the days of getting randomly assigned a map before a match.<!-- --> - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/overwatch-2-new-map-voting-season-17-patch-push-escort-1851785326&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/overwatch-2-new-map-voting-season-17-patch-push-escort-1851785326">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="3b4c2a87bc4213562ed8c56052ee3fae" data-recommend-id="image://3b4c2a87bc4213562ed8c56052ee3fae" data-format="jpg" data-width="1024" data-height="576" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Kong shoots out of a barrel surrounded by thorns. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A Kong shoots out of a barrel surrounded by thorns. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3b4c2a87bc4213562ed8c56052ee3fae" data-recommend-id="image://3b4c2a87bc4213562ed8c56052ee3fae" data-format="jpg" data-width="1024" data-height="576" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Kong shoots out of a barrel surrounded by thorns. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Few moments hit on the original SNES like your first time hearing “Stickerbush Symphony” while shooting through a labyrinth of towering thorny beanstalks in <em>Donkey Kong Country 2</em>'s Bramble Blast levels. It’s one of the best songs to ever appear in a game, alongside one of the most evocative 16-bit platforming levels ever devised. That incredible mashup hasn’t been repeated since, until <em>Donkey Kong Bananza</em>. <!-- --> - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/donkey-kong-bananza-stickerbush-symphony-bramble-blast-1851785457&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/donkey-kong-bananza-stickerbush-symphony-bramble-blast-1851785457">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="c7ef8b24540c2c2054ab36cbd38e7eb0" data-recommend-id="image://c7ef8b24540c2c2054ab36cbd38e7eb0" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Rockstar Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="c7ef8b24540c2c2054ab36cbd38e7eb0" data-recommend-id="image://c7ef8b24540c2c2054ab36cbd38e7eb0" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/red-dead-redemption-2-the-kotaku-review-1829984369&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/red-dead-redemption-2-the-kotaku-review-1829984369"><em>Red Dead Online</em></a></span><em>,</em> Rockstar’s <em>other </em>live-service game that isn’t as popular as <em>Grand Theft Auto Online</em>, isn’t dead. Well, not <em>entirely</em>. The online cowboy simulator just got a small update that adds a few creepy missions and promises more to come later. <!-- --> - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/red-dead-online-undead-nightmare-rdr2-new-zombie-update-1851785429&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/red-dead-online-undead-nightmare-rdr2-new-zombie-update-1851785429">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="9fd680bdda3fe34ac13e18a69b8e366c" data-recommend-id="image://9fd680bdda3fe34ac13e18a69b8e366c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Epic Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="9fd680bdda3fe34ac13e18a69b8e366c" data-recommend-id="image://9fd680bdda3fe34ac13e18a69b8e366c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Buy now, pay later payment provider Affirm has partnered with video game commerce company Xsolla and will soon allow people to pay off in-game purchases of $50 or more via payment plans. <!-- --> - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/buy-now-pay-later-xsolla-fortnite-burrito-payment-plan-1851785550&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/buy-now-pay-later-xsolla-fortnite-burrito-payment-plan-1851785550">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="3a57f23230a38c05ec251bb6d4e9d46c" data-recommend-id="image://3a57f23230a38c05ec251bb6d4e9d46c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1599" data-height="900" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="John Romero sits over a skull. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="John Romero sits over a skull. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Romero Games</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3a57f23230a38c05ec251bb6d4e9d46c" data-recommend-id="image://3a57f23230a38c05ec251bb6d4e9d46c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1599" data-height="900" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="John Romero sits over a skull. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.ign.com/articles/john-romero-co-creator-of-doom-is-making-a-new-fps&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.ign.com/articles/john-romero-co-creator-of-doom-is-making-a-new-fps" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Back in 2022</a></span>, John Romero of <em>Doom</em> fame announced he was working on a new first-person shooter IP in Unreal Engine 5 for a “major publisher.” Three years later, the studio says it’s canceled and employees claim the latest wave of <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/latest-round-of-mass-layoffs-at-xbox-begin-with-200-job-1851785492&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/latest-round-of-mass-layoffs-at-xbox-begin-with-200-job-1851785492">massive cuts at Xbox are to blame</a></span>, with one designer calling the news “[a] massive, sudden &amp; unexpected hit on a Project that was innovative, going strong and most importantly fun.”<!-- --> - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/john-brenda-romero-games-fps-doom-xbox-bethesda-1851785577&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/john-brenda-romero-games-fps-doom-xbox-bethesda-1851785577">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div><br/><br/>https://kotaku.com/kotaku-s-biggest-gaming-culture-news-for-the-week-july-1851785670]]></content:encoded>
